'''Joaquín Piquerez Moreira''' (born 24 August 1998) is a Uruguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[left-back]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] and the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]].

==Club career== 
===Defensor Sporting===
Piquerez played in the youth ranks of the club Defensor Sporting, with which he debuted in the [[Uruguayan Primera División|Uruguayan First Division]] on March 19, 2017 with [[Eduardo Acevedo]] as coach in a match against River Plate that ended in a 1–0 victory. In May, he won the Apertura tournament.<ref>{{Cite thesis |last=BARROSO FURTADO |first=ENRICO |title=O IMPACTO DA ECONOMIA NO FUTEBOL ARGENTINO EM COMPARAÇÃO AO FUTEBOL BRASILEIRO |date=2023 |publisher=Faculdades Catolicas |doi=10.17771/pucrio.acad.70828 }}</ref>

===River Plate===
Piquerez joined River Plate Montevideo, signing a two-year contract.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Esmoris Isoleri |first=Manuel Alfonso |date=2012-03-29 |title=Barrio Peñarol: moderno, industrial, singular. Patrimonialización y reutilización |journal=Labor e Engenho |volume=6 |issue=1 |pages=73–88 |doi=10.20396/lobore.v6i1.20 |issn=2176-8846|doi-access=free }}</ref> He made his debut for his new club on July 14, in a 0–0 draw with [[C.A. Progreso|Progreso]] in the Torneo Intermedio. In August, in the same tournament, Piquerez scored his first goal for River Plate in a 1–1 draw against [[Club Nacional de Football|Nacional]]. River Plate reached the final of the Torneo Intermedio in September, where they drew 2–2 with [[Liverpool F.C. (Montevideo)|Liverpool]], with Piquerez scoring River's first goal. However, Liverpool won 5–4 on penalties, and River Plate finished as runners-up.<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Petiteau |first1=Natalie |last2=Kleisl |first2=Jean-Daniel |date=July 2000 |title=Piquerez S.A. & Ruedin S.A. Le patronat de la boite de montre dans la vallee de Delemont. L'exemple de E. Piquerez S.A. et de G. Ruedin S.A. a Bassecourt (1926-1982) |journal=Le Mouvement Social |issue=192 |page=138 |doi=10.2307/3779751 |jstor=3779751 |issn=0027-2671}}</ref>

===Peñarol===
In January 2020, Peñarol officially announced the signing of Piquerez. The club paid River Plate €300,000 (just under R$1.5 million at the time) for the transfer, and the left-back signed a three-year contract.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Cavalcante |first=Luiz Ricardo |date=2023-11-13 |title=DESIGUALDADES REGIONAIS E FUTEBOL: uma análise da primeira divisão do campeonato brasileiro entre 2003 e 2019 |journal=Gestão & Regionalidade |volume=39 |article-number=e20237996 |doi=10.13037/gr.vol39.e20237996 |issn=2176-5308|doi-access=free }}</ref> Piquerez joined the Peñarol squad on February 12 and made his debut in a 1–2 loss to [[Defensor Sporting]], for[[Uruguayan Primera División|Uruguayan Championship]].<ref>{{Cite thesis |last=Lopez Chirico |first=Selva |title=Uruguai 1985-1993 |date=1995 |publisher=Universidade Estadual de Campinas |doi=10.47749/t/unicamp.1995.99402 }}</ref>

===Palmeiras===
[[File:Piquerez-Palmeiras-Cuiaba-jul-2022.jpg|thumb|left|160px|Piquerez for Palmeiras in 2022]]
On 31 July 2021, Brazilian club [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] announced the signing of Piquerez on a permanent deal until 31 December 2025.<ref>{{cite web|title=PALMEIRAS ACERTA CONTRATAÇÃO DO LATERAL URUGUAIO JOAQUÍN PIQUEREZ|url=https://www.palmeiras.com.br/pt-br/noticias/palmeiras-acerta-contratacao-do-lateral-uruguaio-joaquin-piquerez/|date=31 July 2021|access-date=31 July 2021}}</ref> In November, Piquerez won his first title with Palmeiras. He started in the [[2021 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores de 2021]] final against [[Clube de Regatas Flamengo|Flamengo]], which Palmeiras won 2–1.<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Gabriel Ferreira Miranda |first1=Andreas |last2=Pereira Sanna |first2=Patrícia |last3=Marques Vilella |first3=Rafaela |date=2018-12-01 |title=Teoria do Erro No Direito Penal Brasileiro |journal=Colloquium Socialis |volume=2 |issue=Especial 2 |pages=456–460 |doi=10.5747/cs.2018.v02.nesp2.s0320 |issn=2526-7035|doi-access=free }}</ref>

In the 2022 season, Piquerez established himself as team absolute starter. At the beginning of the year, he won the [[2022 Recopa Sudamericana]] and the [[2022 Campeonato Paulista]]. Three months later, in July, he scored his first goal for Palmeiras, opening the scoring in the second leg of the round of 16, against [[São Paulo FC|São Paulo]], for the [[Copa do Brasil]].<ref>{{Cite thesis |last=Signorelli Miguel |first=Rebeca |title=A escola recebe a Copa do Mundo no Brasil |date=2015 |publisher=Universidade Estadual de Campinas |doi=10.47749/t/unicamp.2015.962335 |hdl=20.500.12733/1627411 |hdl-access=free }}</ref> In the same match, the full-back completed 100 appearances for Palmeiras for Palmeiras.<ref>{{Cite thesis |last=Silva |first=Marco Antonio da |title=Por uma pedagogia do palhaço: riso, corpo jogador, transgressão e inversão |publisher=Universidade de Sao Paulo, Agencia USP de Gestao da Informacao Academica (AGUIA) |url=https://doi.org/10.11606/d.48.2017.tde-14122016-151218}}</ref> In November, Piquerez won the [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Campeonato Brasileiro Série A 2022]] and was named to [[Prêmio Craque do Brasileirão|Campeonato Brasileiro Série A Team of the Year]]. That following season, he won the [[2023 Campeonato Paulista]] and the [[2023 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|2023 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]], being again a pillar of the team.<ref>{{Cite thesis |last=NÓBREGA LA MARCA |first=CAIO |title=ANÁLISE COMPARATIVA FINANCEIRA ENTRE FLAMENGO E PALMEIRAS |date=2018 |publisher=Faculdades Catolicas |doi=10.17771/pucrio.acad.35167 }}</ref>

==International career==
Piquerez has represented Uruguay at various youth levels.<ref>{{cite web|title=19 - Joaquín Piquerez|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/19-joaquin-piquerez/|access-date=26 May 2021}}</ref> He was part of national team squads at the [[2015 South American U-17 Championship]] and the [[Football at the 2019 Pan American Games – Men's tournament|2019 Pan American Games]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Datos del plantel panamericano de Uruguay|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/datos-del-plantel-panamericano-de-uruguay/|date=29 June 2019|access-date=26 May 2021}}</ref> In December 2019, he was called up to [[Uruguay Olympic football team|under-23 team]] for the [[2020 CONMEBOL Pre-Olympic Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Gustavo Ferreyra definió el plantel para el Torneo Preolímpico 2020|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/gustavo-ferreyra-definio-el-plantel-para-el-torneo-preolimpico-2020/|date=29 December 2019|access-date=26 May 2021}}</ref>

Piquerez received his first call-up to the [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay national team]] on 28 May 2021 for [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches. However, he got injured the following day and was replaced by [[Camilo Cándido]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Camilo Cándido convocado|url=https://www.auf.org.uy/camilo-candido-convocado/|date=30 May 2021|access-date=5 September 2021}}</ref> He made his senior team debut on 2 September 2021 in a 1–1 draw against [[Peru national football team|Peru]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Joaquín Piquerez estuvo a centímetros de redondear un debut increíble|url=https://www.ovaciondigital.com.uy/futbol/joaquin-piquerez-estuvo-centimetros-redondear-debut-increible.html|date=3 September 2021|access-date=5 September 2021}}</ref> On 31 May 2026, he was named in Uruguay's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Mundial 2026: Uruguay dio a conocer la lista de 26 convocados por Marcelo Bielsa|url=https://www.montevideo.com.uy/Deportes/Mundial-2026-Uruguay-dio-a-conocer-la-lista-de-26-convocados-por-Marcelo-Bielsa-uc963756|language=es|date=31 May 2026|access-date=31 May 2026}}</ref>

